==English==

===Etymology===
From Italian [[Italia#Italian|Italia]] < Latin [[Italia#Latin|Ītalia]], via Greek from [[Oscan]] ''Víteliú'' (a name for the southwestern tip of the boot of Italy), meaning "land of bulls" in Oscan; usually assumed to be a cognate of Latin [[vitulus|vĭtŭlus]] '[[calf]]', despite the different length of the ''i''.

===Proper noun===
'''Italy'''

# A country in southern [[Europe]], one of the states of the [[European Union]]. Official name: The Italian Republic (in Italian, ''la Repubblica Italiana'').

